title: Grateful Dead Live at Community War Memorial Auditorium on 1984-04-16
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Cassidy, West L.A. Fadeaway-> Might As Well

Set 2

Hell In A Bucket, Ship of Fools, Far From Me-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Day Job

reviews.review_text:
Spring of 1984 This show was recorded right behind the sound board. It was a general admission show, as all shows at the War Memorial were. This is the same system that was used at Niagara Falls and in the summer at Kingston Wonderland!

Great time were had and as I was in college they were enjoyed to the max!!!!!! So glad I experienced them and wish that I could do it all over again!
